1
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,430
Due to the absence

2
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:16,280
of a father figure in his birth family,

3
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,210
the killer developed
deep-seated inferiority

4
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:19,940
and an extreme craving for love

5
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:20,980
and attention.

6
00:00:21,550 --> 00:00:22,610
I also believe that

7
00:00:23,030 --> 00:00:25,230
he was abandoned by his mother
at some point.

8
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:26,760
How is it? Handsome, right?

9
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:29,570
Where did you get these videos?

10
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:31,660
Didn't you tell me

11
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:32,670
about Professor Jiang's

12
00:00:32,670 --> 00:00:33,350
prime-time

13
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:34,760
legal program interview?

14
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:35,490
So I found it.

15
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,490
I searched too. How come I didn't find it?

16
00:00:37,490 --> 00:00:39,430
How could you possibly find it online?

17
00:00:39,430 --> 00:00:41,030
I asked the TV station for it.

18
00:00:41,390 --> 00:00:42,720
I made a copy of it. Here.

19
00:00:43,140 --> 00:00:45,030
Historical records of
the National Little Rose.

20
00:00:45,030 --> 00:00:45,790
What the heck?

21
00:00:45,790 --> 00:00:47,390
Na-National Little Rose?

22
00:00:47,870 --> 00:00:49,390
At that time, the TV station

23
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:50,780
didn't know Professor Jiang's name,

24
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:51,790
but they were deeply impressed by him

25
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:53,470
and his red suit.

26
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:54,710
So they gave him this nickname,

27
00:00:54,710 --> 00:00:56,640
and it stuck around.

28
00:00:58,260 --> 00:01:00,060
National Little Rose.

29
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:01,520
But now

30
00:01:01,540 --> 00:01:03,690
he's been privatized by you.

31
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:38,040
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

32
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:40,900
[Episode 15]

33
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:42,340
Mr. Wang.

34
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,010
Hit a snag, didn't you?

35
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:52,230
I told you not to come today,

36
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,680
but you wouldn't listen.

37
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:55,960
You might be a godsend elsewhere,

38
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,960
but here,

39
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,120
you're a total jinx.

40
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,310
Don't you know that?

41
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,840
And why on earth is that?

42
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,470
Ask him.

43
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,190
The case was already solved back then.

44
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:06,590
It was my appeal material

45
00:03:06,650 --> 00:03:08,910
handed directly to
the provincial procuratorate

46
00:03:08,910 --> 00:03:10,570
that made them take a big fall.

47
00:03:11,790 --> 00:03:13,390
You can't be blamed for that.

48
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,700
Are you done with your PDA?

49
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,200
If so, let's get down to business.

50
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:23,329
Alright,

51
00:03:23,329 --> 00:03:24,970
don't count on them for this.

52
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,280
About what you told me last time—
that you suspected

53
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,710
Qi Yan might be a twin—

54
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:31,260
I've actually found some clues.

55
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:33,340
Want to hear them?

56
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:37,590
It's been 20 years.

57
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:40,530
I'm already retired,

58
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,550
and you still come to bother me.

59
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:43,960
That's a bit too much, Director.

60
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,360
What do you mean by bothering you?

61
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:47,320
I'm just asking you to recall something.

62
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,970
You coming back to ask me

63
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:51,450
means this case

64
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:52,840
has hit a dead end, right?

65
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,030
What do you mean by hitting a dead end?

66
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:55,079
Isn't this a new clue right here?

67
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,010
Take a good look.

68
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:57,730
Look.

69
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,630
"The perpetrator

70
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:08,030
has serious cognitive bias against women.

71
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:10,580
Single-parent family..."

72
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:14,060
Alright, that's enough.

73
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:15,720
Let me ask you,

74
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:18,670
you've been in the Xiacheng District
for decades.

75
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:21,360
Has there been a family

76
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:23,970
with a woman raising a child

77
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:26,530
but unable to support the child?

78
00:04:26,870 --> 00:04:28,110
Think carefully.

79
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,610
I need time to think.

80
00:04:39,190 --> 00:04:41,050
Do you remember the first victim?

81
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:42,830
Yes, I do.

82
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:44,960
Going back a few years,

83
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:47,470
when we were visiting that area,

84
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:51,090
we checked the whole neighborhood
around there—

85
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,330
every corner of it.

86
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:53,950
And you know what?

87
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:56,720
One of the households told me

88
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:58,510
that their house

89
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,950
was for rent,

90
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,430
and they once

91
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,070
rented it to a woman.

92
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,800
That woman was exceptionally beautiful,

93
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,860
so they remembered her very clearly.

94
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:07,870
They told me

95
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:08,830
that that woman

96
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:09,870
had no job

97
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:11,080
and rarely went out.

98
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:13,570
But different men kept coming to see her.

99
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:15,080
Prostitution?

100
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,810
We couldn't be sure about that.

101
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,960
I remember 2 of her neighbors

102
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:22,070
kept gossiping to me,

103
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,250
saying things like

104
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:24,430
that family

105
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:25,920
took in an unclean woman

106
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:28,190
who earned dirty money.

107
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,360
Did she have a son?

108
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:31,360
Yes.

109
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,930
Two sons, twins.

110
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,300
Did you look into that woman?

111
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,159
You must be hungry, right?

112
00:05:41,230 --> 00:05:43,760
After the vice squad got the report
back then,

113
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:45,450
they went to check,

114
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:48,470
only to find she had moved out
early that morning.

115
00:05:48,830 --> 00:05:50,870
Besides knowing she was pretty,

116
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:53,490
they didn't even have a photo of her.

117
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:54,680
Plus,

118
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:56,540
the landlord hadn't signed

119
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,320
a formal lease with her,

120
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:01,130
so there was no further information.

121
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,800
Even the fact that she had twin sons

122
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:05,290
was only discovered by the landlord

123
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:06,170
by accident.

124
00:06:06,870 --> 00:06:07,800
At that time, the landlord

125
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,310
told me a story.

126
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:10,920
He said one day

127
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:12,750
he went to read the water meter,

128
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,810
and no one was home.

129
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,630
He saw on the living room table

130
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:16,600
a photo.

131
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:19,510
Since the woman was very pretty,

132
00:06:19,990 --> 00:06:21,850
he took a closer look at the photo.

133
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:22,800
He said

134
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,520
it was a photo of that woman
and her two sons.

135
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,070
The two sons looked exactly the same.

136
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:32,200
So that means

137
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:33,550
he only saw the photo

138
00:06:33,570 --> 00:06:36,170
and never actually met the children
in person?

139
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,040
The current statements

140
00:06:39,390 --> 00:06:41,310
all lack substantial evidence.

141
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:43,400
All the information comes from

142
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:46,220
the one-sided stories of
the landlord and neighbors.

143
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:47,950
So it could only be left at that.

144
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,310
Alright, tomorrow,

145
00:06:49,390 --> 00:06:50,840
I'll go to the branch again

146
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,409
and have them check
the birth certificates.

147
00:06:52,409 --> 00:06:53,409
If they're twins,

148
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,310
the scope

149
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:55,810
shouldn't be too large.

150
00:06:55,810 --> 00:06:56,940
I already checked.

151
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,700
No one matched the criminal profile.

152
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,060
Do we have the address of
the place that woman rented?

153
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:02,530
Yes.

154
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:05,850
Since we can't find information
on the children, let's try the mother.

155
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:08,240
Is it really necessary
to go find the landlord?

156
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,480
No need to find the landlord.

157
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,410
Let's track down

158
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,290
the pimps operating in that area.

159
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,430
As for this matter you're investigating,

160
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:20,120
you don't even have a clear target.

161
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,390
It's been 20 to 30 years.

162
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:23,870
Where do you expect me
to find these people for you?

163
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:26,000
There must at least be some records of
vice sweeps, right?

164
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,160
We plan to start screening
people with prior criminal records.

165
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:28,820
Captain Li,

166
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:29,830
what do you think?

167
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,310
The computer records only go up to 2000.

168
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,510
What you want to check

169
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:36,280
is way past that time frame,
my dear comrades.

170
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,240
There must be paper records, right?

171
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,640
Hopefully the mice haven't chewed them up.

172
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,000
Li,

173
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,870
we won't hold you up...

174
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:44,600
Don't try to get chummy with me.

175
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,510
Let me tell you,

176
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,380
you've got no clout

177
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:47,430
with me!

178
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:57,630
The two of us really screwed him over
back in the day.

179
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,390
To this day,

180
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:01,040
he still hasn't been promoted.

181
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:10,200
Everything's here.

182
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:12,950
Leaders,

183
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,950
don't blame me for not assisting you.

184
00:08:14,950 --> 00:08:16,000
As you can see,

185
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,390
I'm short on manpower here.

186
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:19,000
I hope you can understand.

187
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,070
I'll leave Xu with you.

188
00:08:21,630 --> 00:08:22,740
He'll dig through all this with you guys

189
00:08:22,740 --> 00:08:25,070
like searching for a needle in a haystack.

190
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,680
If you can find anything this way,

191
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,340
I'll admit you've got skills.

192
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,530
I've got other cases to work on.

193
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:30,130
Pardon me.

194
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:37,720
Li is right.

195
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:39,760
This is no easy task.

196
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,040
How about this?

197
00:08:59,040 --> 00:08:59,960
Let's split up.

198
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,630
I'm familiar with
the vice sweep side of things.

199
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:02,940
I'll go out on the streets
and feel things out.

200
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:04,510
You guys keep sifting through
the files here—

201
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:06,390
focus on checking what

202
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:07,670
those with prior records are doing now.

203
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:08,840
Pull out the ones

204
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,200
who've been hanging around the same area

205
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,200
for 20 to 30 years.

206
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,840
Maybe we'll find some clues.

207
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,720
Zhou's idea is not bad.

208
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,600
I'll go with you then.

209
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,120
I'm okay on my own.

210
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,380
I can cover for you.

211
00:09:32,470 --> 00:09:33,700
Take him. Take him.

212
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,530
Go ahead.

213
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,640
I've got this.

214
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:36,550
Alright.

215
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:37,790
Let's go.

216
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,360
Mr. Wang, we'll head out first.

217
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,000
Okay.

218
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:02,550
I'll take the left.

219
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:03,360
You take the right.

220
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,600
Let's meet at the intersection later.

221
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,080
Okay.

222
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,980
Hey, handsome.

223
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,570
Buy a balloon for your girlfriend.

224
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,960
We're already married.

225
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:14,110
Then buy it for your kid.

226
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:21,880
I'll wait for you
at the intersection ahead.

227
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,040
Handsome.

228
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:24,070
Buy one.

229
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,200
Both boys and girls love it.

230
00:10:26,570 --> 00:10:27,440
Check out this doggy.

231
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,680
Isn't it pretty?

232
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,440
Hansheng, where are you?

233
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,680
The doggy's so cute.

234
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,620
Is it for me?

235
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:11,600
Let's go upstairs and chat for a while.

236
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:12,790
Come on.

237
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:14,390
It's fine.

238
00:11:14,730 --> 00:11:16,390
Where are you from, handsome?

239
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:18,670
He already rejected you,

240
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,460
Miss.

241
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,460
Who are you?

242
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,520
Why did you grab me?

243
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,180
I hate it most when other women

244
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,070
get handsy with him.

245
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:28,610
What's your name?

246
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:32,030
Entrapment, huh?

247
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,030
You guys really went all out.

248
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:35,700
Just answer the questions.

249
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,360
Or do you want me to take you in?

250
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,040
Name.

251
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:40,970
Feifei.

252
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:41,790
Real name.

253
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,120
Feifei...

254
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:44,900
Li.

255
00:11:46,370 --> 00:11:47,170
What do you do?

256
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,930
You caught me,
and you're asking what I do?

257
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,210
I should be asking you that question.

258
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:53,090
Be serious.

259
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,960
We want to ask you something.

260
00:11:58,510 --> 00:12:00,030
So you're not the vice squad?

261
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:01,320
I knew it.

262
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,890
I recognize the cops around here.

263
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,510
I've never seen a woman in the vice squad.

264
00:12:07,510 --> 00:12:08,360
I want to know—

265
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:10,260
who manages you guys?

266
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:11,570
Why should I tell you?

267
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:12,610
So someone does.

268
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,900
I was just saying that.

269
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,320
Hansheng.

270
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:24,240
Spit it out.

271
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:26,550
Well,

272
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:28,790
I usually find my clients myself,

273
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,250
but some

274
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:32,040
are referred to me by others.

275
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:33,150
800 a client,

276
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:34,430
and they take a 300 cut.

277
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:35,760
So who assigns you the work?

278
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:36,550
Hong.

279
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,030
Hong?

280
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,440
What's his full name?

281
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:41,080
I just know him as Hong.

282
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,290
It's not like we're students at school—

283
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,600
who uses full names?

284
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,950
How long has he been in this line of work?

285
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:49,390
He's always been doing this, I think.

286
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,730
Longer than me, anyway.

287
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:09,120
Is this him?

288
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:10,200
Named Hong Cheng.

289
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,260
Bring him in for questioning.

290
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:16,470
Well...

291
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,720
What's so hard about that?

292
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:22,320
It's not like we're searching for a needle
in a haystack anymore.

293
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,000
Li?

294
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:28,390
Li!

295
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,600
Um,

296
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,910
Wang.

297
00:13:45,710 --> 00:13:47,370
Officer Zhou, Officer Jiang.

298
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:48,800
Hong Cheng

299
00:13:48,850 --> 00:13:49,510
confessed.

300
00:13:50,410 --> 00:13:52,340
Over 20 years ago, that area

301
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:53,980
was run by one of his senior guys,

302
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:55,340
named Yu Liang,

303
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:57,070
who was involved in this line of work.

304
00:13:57,070 --> 00:13:58,110
That Yu Liang

305
00:13:58,130 --> 00:13:59,390
did time for a few years

306
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,610
and is out now.

307
00:14:01,850 --> 00:14:03,380
Did you ask about the twins?

308
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,080
I did.

309
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,680
This is the key part.

310
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:07,610
Hong Cheng

311
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,000
once heard Yu Liang brag

312
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,630
that when he was young,

313
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:13,740
he dated a woman

314
00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:15,030
who was raising twins.

315
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,860
Do we have Yu Liang's address?

316
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:18,980
Yes, it's here.

317
00:14:21,710 --> 00:14:23,510
I printed out a copy of
all the information

318
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:24,640
I could find for you.

319
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:26,730
Thank you.

320
00:14:29,570 --> 00:14:30,380
Li.

321
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:35,260
So I've still got some clout
with you, right?

322
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:36,420
What do you mean you've got clout?

323
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:39,550
I'm doing this out of respect
for Officer Zhou, alright?

324
00:14:42,660 --> 00:14:44,140
Li. Li!

325
00:14:48,070 --> 00:14:49,950
I know who you are looking for.

326
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:52,180
It's Qi Zhen.

327
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:55,140
Back when I first met Qi Zhen,

328
00:14:55,690 --> 00:14:56,890
she came to Huaiguang

329
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:58,240
to make a living

330
00:14:59,180 --> 00:15:00,580
and stepped onto my turf.

331
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,500
As soon as she arrived,

332
00:15:03,310 --> 00:15:04,870
the girls working under me

333
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:07,190
couldn't get any business.

334
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:08,510
So,

335
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:11,010
I went to her place to cause trouble.

336
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:12,290
The moment I saw her,

337
00:15:12,290 --> 00:15:13,120
I understood.

338
00:15:14,730 --> 00:15:16,130
Zhen was very beautiful,

339
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:18,740
the kind of woman

340
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:21,270
any man would be captivated by

341
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,570
at first sight.

342
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:25,060
Later,

343
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,500
I went to cause trouble a few more times.

344
00:15:29,610 --> 00:15:31,300
Unexpectedly, we ended up

345
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:33,920
becoming familiar with each other.

346
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:35,050
I only found out then

347
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,560
that she wasn't alone—

348
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:38,910
she was with a child,

349
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:41,780
her own child.

350
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:44,810
They were originally twins,

351
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,020
but the older brother had died,

352
00:15:47,020 --> 00:15:48,950
leaving just the younger brother.

353
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:51,400
What was the child's name?

354
00:15:53,140 --> 00:15:53,970
I don't know

355
00:15:54,970 --> 00:15:55,780
his full name.

356
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:58,610
His nickname was

357
00:16:00,180 --> 00:16:01,140
either An...

358
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:03,970
Or Yan.

359
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:06,310
Zhen was very sensitive about people

360
00:16:06,310 --> 00:16:07,640
asking about her child,

361
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,850
so I didn't ask much.

362
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:10,710
Why was she sensitive?

363
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:12,120
She was worried

364
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:14,970
that the child would be taken away.

365
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:15,850
I remember

366
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:17,540
one night,

367
00:16:18,090 --> 00:16:19,020
it was raining,

368
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:21,330
she came banging on my door in a panic,

369
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,620
saying the child had gone missing.

370
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:25,060
Seeing her so anxious,

371
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,220
I picked up the phone

372
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:27,370
to call the police.

373
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:29,180
To my surprise, she suddenly snatched

374
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,380
the phone from me,

375
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:31,710
refusing to let me do it.

376
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:33,540
Well, Zhen had

377
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:35,420
lost a son

378
00:16:35,730 --> 00:16:37,190
and had been traumatized.

379
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:38,020
You know,

380
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:40,350
she was a bit neurotic up here.

381
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:42,290
She always felt someone

382
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:44,350
was going to take this child away too.

383
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:45,450
Later, I

384
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:47,060
found the child

385
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:48,570
in her closet.

386
00:16:49,690 --> 00:16:50,350
In a closet?

387
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:51,020
Yeah.

388
00:16:51,730 --> 00:16:53,020
Right... In a closet.

389
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:55,660
So this child—

390
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:58,850
how old was he then? Was he in school?

391
00:16:59,610 --> 00:17:00,420
At the time,

392
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:02,610
I think he was about 10 years old.

393
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:04,560
He didn't go to school.

394
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:06,099
Zhen wouldn't allow it,

395
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:07,730
and she wouldn't let him go outside
either.

396
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:09,660
They just stayed at home every day.

397
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,220
She said she'd teach him herself.

398
00:17:10,020 --> 00:17:17,880
[1989]

399
00:17:12,730 --> 00:17:13,619
Sometimes,

400
00:17:14,050 --> 00:17:14,970
when Zhen

401
00:17:15,540 --> 00:17:16,780
was sewing clothes

402
00:17:17,530 --> 00:17:18,940
or doing handicrafts,

403
00:17:19,420 --> 00:17:21,050
the kid would watch her.

404
00:17:21,619 --> 00:17:23,220
Zhen liked to play the piano,

405
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:25,869
and the kid liked to listen to her.

406
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:27,819
I think

407
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:30,900
that must have been
the biggest entertainment

408
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,160
for the mother and son.

409
00:17:32,670 --> 00:17:33,260
Is it pretty?

410
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:33,940
Yes.

411
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,330
The mother and son
had a very close relationship.

412
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:39,040
That kid

413
00:17:40,290 --> 00:17:41,180
was hardly

414
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:44,380
ever out of Zhen's sight.

415
00:17:46,290 --> 00:17:47,140
Even...

416
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:53,040
Even when

417
00:17:53,420 --> 00:17:55,480
someone came to their house to visit,

418
00:17:55,590 --> 00:17:56,790
she would find a place

419
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:58,970
to hide that kid.

420
00:18:24,660 --> 00:18:26,460
You're in quite a good mood, huh?

421
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:29,940
I like the dark.

422
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:36,530
Jiang Cheng.

423
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:40,340
Do you know what it feels like
to be locked

424
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:41,870
in a dark, enclosed closet?

425
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:45,820
Suffocated?

426
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:46,900
Scared?

427
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:03,680
I like the night.

428
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:06,250
It makes you feel safe—

429
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:09,830
like an owl in the darkness.

430
00:19:11,830 --> 00:19:13,140
Only you can see

431
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:14,860
and hear.

432
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:18,700
The whole world seems to be
under your control.

433
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:20,490
Yet

434
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:24,370
no one even knows you exist.

435
00:19:45,660 --> 00:19:46,720
Please take a look.

436
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:47,660
Is this Qi Yan?

437
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,720
T-This is too blurry.

438
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:51,770
Besides,

439
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:53,750
he was just a kid back then.

440
00:19:54,970 --> 00:19:55,940
I can't tell.

441
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,900
Then do you know where Qi Zhen is now?

442
00:20:02,450 --> 00:20:02,940
I...

443
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:04,860
I thought you knew.

444
00:20:06,490 --> 00:20:07,490
The mother and son

445
00:20:07,690 --> 00:20:09,550
have been missing for many years.

446
00:20:11,450 --> 00:20:12,420
Do you remember

447
00:20:12,490 --> 00:20:13,940
where you saw her

448
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:15,140
for the last time?

449
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:17,050
I can't remember

450
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:19,510
when it was clearly.

451
00:20:19,690 --> 00:20:20,940
I think

452
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:24,050
it was in 1992.

453
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:26,820
But I remember the place very clearly.

454
00:20:26,820 --> 00:20:28,480
It was in Huaiguang Hospital.

455
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:29,380
She was sent to the hospital

456
00:20:29,380 --> 00:20:30,050
because

457
00:20:30,770 --> 00:20:32,370
she tried to commit suicide.

458
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,710
By slitting her wrists?

459
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:36,820
Yes.

460
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:38,730
I

461
00:20:39,690 --> 00:20:41,420
went to the hospital to see her.

462
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:42,950
She was lying in the bed,

463
00:20:44,470 --> 00:20:45,730
her face deathly pale.

464
00:20:46,610 --> 00:20:48,270
I tried to talk sense into her.

465
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:49,180
I said,

466
00:20:50,530 --> 00:20:52,010
"Even if you won't think for yourself,

467
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:53,280
you have to think for your kid.

468
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,210
What will happen to him if you die?"

469
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:56,590
She

470
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,010
didn't say a word.

471
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,030
Just lying there.

472
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:02,660
There was no light

473
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:04,380
in her eyes at all,

474
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,070
like a living dead.

475
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:09,710
Fortunately, at that time,

476
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:11,240
the police officers

477
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:12,560
were going door to door

478
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:14,920
conducting a household survey.

479
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:16,530
Otherwise,

480
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:18,550
she would have died.

481
00:21:19,730 --> 00:21:20,420
Later,

482
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:23,040
when I went to the hospital again,

483
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:25,730
Zhen was gone.

484
00:21:26,530 --> 00:21:28,260
I asked the doctors and nurses.

485
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:29,530
They said

486
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,160
she sneaked away by herself,

487
00:21:31,860 --> 00:21:33,860
and they didn't know where she went.

488
00:21:37,580 --> 00:21:38,640
From that point on,

489
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,700
she just vanished into thin air.

490
00:21:43,490 --> 00:21:43,970
I...

491
00:21:45,730 --> 00:21:46,690
But I always feel

492
00:21:47,820 --> 00:21:48,820
she's not dead—

493
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:51,380
that she's still alive.

494
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:52,820
Maybe

495
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,340
she didn't go far at all.

496
00:21:55,580 --> 00:21:57,640
Maybe she's right here in Huaiguang.

497
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:58,760
Over the years,

498
00:21:58,900 --> 00:21:59,660
I think

499
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:01,930
I've seen her a few times.

500
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:04,030
Once, from a distance,

501
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:06,450
I saw her right at the alley entrance.

502
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:07,510
But when I ran over,

503
00:22:09,210 --> 00:22:09,940
she was gone.

504
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,450
Once on the street,

505
00:22:12,450 --> 00:22:14,620
it felt like we brushed past each other.

506
00:22:14,620 --> 00:22:16,020
But when I turned my head,

507
00:22:17,430 --> 00:22:18,430
she disappeared.

508
00:22:19,490 --> 00:22:21,050
I can't tell if it was

509
00:22:21,050 --> 00:22:23,340
my hallucination or if I really saw her.

510
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:24,380
You see,

511
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:25,250
a woman—

512
00:22:25,530 --> 00:22:26,380
for her child—

513
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:29,050
was willing to do anything
and had done everything.

514
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:30,770
She already knew no limit.

515
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:32,160
But why...

516
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:34,560
Why would she commit suicide?

517
00:22:34,940 --> 00:22:37,940
What would happen to the child
if she really died? I...

518
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:41,650
I just don't understand.

519
00:22:42,490 --> 00:22:43,720
In your memory,

520
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:46,200
did Qi Zhen ever wear red clothes?

521
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:46,900
Yes.

522
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:50,770
She liked red.

523
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:52,730
She made most of

524
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:54,260
her own dresses herself.

525
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:57,400
They were very beautiful.

526
00:23:00,740 --> 00:23:04,310
Qi Zhen attempted suicide
by slitting her wrists when she was young.

527
00:23:04,310 --> 00:23:05,700
In all of our cases,

528
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,550
the fatal wounds on the victims' wrists

529
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,930
are a consistent criminal signature.

530
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:12,580
Chief Tan.

531
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,060
During the process of
committing the crimes, Qi Yan

532
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,440
kept setting up

533
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:18,460
scenes filled with ritualistic elements.

534
00:23:18,460 --> 00:23:19,730
It should be a projection of the scene

535
00:23:19,730 --> 00:23:21,430
when his mother slit her wrists
to commit suicide.

536
00:23:21,430 --> 00:23:22,830
By recreating the scene,

537
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:24,860
he repeatedly brings himself back to
that moment,

538
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:25,660
seeking

539
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:27,190
some kind of psychological

540
00:23:27,190 --> 00:23:28,560
comfort and relief.

541
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:30,890
But I still haven't figured out

542
00:23:30,890 --> 00:23:31,820
why he does this.

543
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:34,100
Generally speaking,

544
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,230
painful memories

545
00:23:35,410 --> 00:23:37,360
aren't something people deliberately
try to repeat,

546
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,490
and killing isn't meant to be
a form of self-torture.

547
00:23:39,490 --> 00:23:41,640
The reason that drove Qi Zhen
to attempt suicide,

548
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,470
and the reason Qi Yan

549
00:23:42,470 --> 00:23:44,470
kept recreating the suicide scene—

550
00:23:44,620 --> 00:23:46,610
if we can figure out these two things,

551
00:23:46,610 --> 00:23:47,940
then psychologically,

552
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:51,000
we can completely get a handle on
Qi Yan as a person.

553
00:23:51,060 --> 00:23:52,590
I understand what you mean.

554
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,480
Mentor.

555
00:23:54,730 --> 00:23:56,570
We want to go meet

556
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,730
the police officer
who helped Qi Zhen back then.

557
00:23:58,730 --> 00:23:59,530
Sure.

558
00:24:00,010 --> 00:24:02,540
Just go straight to
the local police station.

559
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:04,420
There shouldn't be many people
in charge of household registration.

560
00:24:04,420 --> 00:24:05,980
He should be easy enough to find.

561
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,510
Well, you may not know this,

562
00:24:07,970 --> 00:24:09,380
but our Professor Jiang

563
00:24:10,180 --> 00:24:12,510
isn't exactly welcome here in Huaiguang.

564
00:24:12,580 --> 00:24:15,180
We've already run into
quite a few roadblocks.

565
00:24:17,210 --> 00:24:18,210
I didn't expect

566
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:20,530
Professor Jiang to have times
when things don't go his way.

567
00:24:20,530 --> 00:24:21,140
It's fine.

568
00:24:21,210 --> 00:24:22,370
I'll talk to them.

569
00:24:22,820 --> 00:24:24,450
We'll just send an official letter,

570
00:24:24,450 --> 00:24:25,010
alright?

571
00:24:25,690 --> 00:24:28,040
Now that we finally have
conclusive evidence,

572
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,580
no one will dare to delay the case.

573
00:24:29,580 --> 00:24:30,140
Okay.

574
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:31,970
Anything else?

575
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:35,860
Mentor,

576
00:24:35,970 --> 00:24:38,320
there's nothing else.

577
00:24:38,660 --> 00:24:39,290
Okay then.

578
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:43,090
Finding out about Qi Zhen

579
00:24:43,140 --> 00:24:44,200
was not easy at all.

580
00:24:44,530 --> 00:24:45,990
Thanks for your hard work.

581
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:47,700
Alright. Please rest early.

582
00:24:47,790 --> 00:24:49,380
Alright. Bye.

583
00:24:51,180 --> 00:24:51,730
Gosh.

584
00:24:51,730 --> 00:24:53,440
My mentor is way too talkative.

585
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,580
We talked for over half an hour.

586
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:55,910
Get me a bottle of water.

587
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:07,450
You smell so good.

588
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:09,280
It's a floral scent today.

589
00:25:09,730 --> 00:25:11,990
I'm the National Little Rose, after all.

590
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:14,230
Professor Jiang,

591
00:25:14,230 --> 00:25:15,690
so you know how to joke now.

592
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:17,020
I always have.

593
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,180
He's lying.

594
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:27,080
Zhou Jin,

595
00:25:28,690 --> 00:25:30,290
I thought you booked one room

596
00:25:30,820 --> 00:25:32,620
because you wanted to be with me.

597
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:36,010
I am with you.

598
00:25:39,290 --> 00:25:40,010
Are you?

599
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:53,760
Let's go to bed.

600
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:11,350
I didn't mean to.

601
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:14,050
There were really no other rooms left—

602
00:26:14,050 --> 00:26:15,510
only a standard twin room.

603
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,140
Besides,

604
00:26:17,860 --> 00:26:19,190
you are a light sleeper.

605
00:26:20,070 --> 00:26:22,130
I want you to sleep more comfortably.

606
00:26:23,730 --> 00:26:25,660
How do you know I'm a light sleeper?

607
00:26:28,410 --> 00:26:30,730
When two people have been together
for a long time,

608
00:26:30,730 --> 00:26:32,930
they know everything about each other.

609
00:26:46,860 --> 00:26:48,210
Why do you think Yu Liang

610
00:26:52,650 --> 00:26:54,930
cares so much about Qi Zhen?

611
00:26:56,420 --> 00:26:58,220
He's waited for her for 20 years.

612
00:26:58,790 --> 00:27:01,320
It can't just be because
she's pretty, right?

613
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:06,890
I guess everyone has their own obsession.

614
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,000
But I could tell

615
00:27:12,470 --> 00:27:14,270
that he's truly waiting for her.

616
00:27:14,450 --> 00:27:16,310
He could even wait for a lifetime.

617
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:19,600
If it were you,

618
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,930
would you be willing to do that?

619
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:25,520
I have waited.

620
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:29,440
Then I understood a saying,

621
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,490
"People who can bravely

622
00:27:37,130 --> 00:27:38,450
say goodbye

623
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:42,600
will be rewarded with a new beginning."

624
00:27:52,180 --> 00:27:53,640
Turn off the light, Hubby.

625
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:05,650
What did you just call me?

626
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:08,940
Hubby.

627
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:24,750
Jiang Hansheng,

628
00:28:26,970 --> 00:28:28,420
you're a good husband.

629
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:34,380
Zhou Jin.

630
00:28:36,510 --> 00:28:38,240
When we have kids in the future,

631
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:40,090
what should we name them?

632
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:45,250
I think I will be a qualified father.

633
00:29:22,850 --> 00:29:26,370
[Yatou Pharmaceutical Factory]

634
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:32,000
We're here.

635
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:34,340
Untie our new friend.

636
00:29:36,870 --> 00:29:37,400
Hands.

637
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:49,070
Get out of the car.

638
00:30:03,290 --> 00:30:04,160
Where is this?

639
00:30:10,790 --> 00:30:12,390
Are you going to kill me here?

640
00:30:15,930 --> 00:30:16,730
Old Scorpion,

641
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,920
you didn't keep your word.

642
00:30:31,130 --> 00:30:33,460
You did a good job with
what I told you to do.

643
00:30:33,740 --> 00:30:34,370
Qiu Ye,

644
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:36,050
Boss He, and Qi

645
00:30:36,870 --> 00:30:38,470
all strongly recommend you.

646
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:41,230
Looks like I should give you a chance.

647
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:43,170
Qi?

648
00:30:44,580 --> 00:30:45,380
That's right.

649
00:30:45,600 --> 00:30:46,490
Qi.

650
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:50,990
Who exactly are you?

651
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:54,490
Jiang Cheng,

652
00:30:55,770 --> 00:30:57,100
welcome on board.

653
00:31:00,940 --> 00:31:02,100
I am Old Scorpion.

654
00:31:08,410 --> 00:31:09,010
By the way,

655
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:12,580
your marksmanship is just so-so.

656
00:31:12,740 --> 00:31:14,670
I'll give you some guidance later.

657
00:31:19,660 --> 00:31:20,230
Let's go.

658
00:31:32,210 --> 00:31:32,770
Zhou Jin,

659
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:34,580
I will send you some files,

660
00:31:34,610 --> 00:31:36,180
including the police dispatch records

661
00:31:36,180 --> 00:31:36,660
and

662
00:31:37,050 --> 00:31:38,450
the contact information
of the police officer

663
00:31:38,450 --> 00:31:40,100
who saved Qi Zhen back then.

664
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:42,240
The officer is called Jian Liang.

665
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:43,060
Over 20 years ago,

666
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:45,340
he was a household registration officer
in the Xiacheng District of Huaiguang.

667
00:31:45,340 --> 00:31:46,890
Later, he was transferred to
Huiping County

668
00:31:46,890 --> 00:31:51,930
[Huiping, Jingzhou]

669
00:31:47,100 --> 00:31:49,200
and became the head of the police station.

670
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,400
Huiping isn't far. You can drive there.

671
00:31:51,410 --> 00:31:52,530
It only takes an hour.

672
00:31:52,530 --> 00:31:54,060
He will cooperate with you.

673
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:57,670
Is this Chief Jian?

674
00:31:57,900 --> 00:31:58,820
I am Zhou Jin

675
00:31:58,970 --> 00:32:00,730
from the Nancheng Branch of Haizhou City.

676
00:32:00,730 --> 00:32:01,420
Hello.

677
00:32:02,530 --> 00:32:03,860
What case is it exactly?

678
00:32:06,620 --> 00:32:08,660
We'd like to talk to you in person.

679
00:32:09,210 --> 00:32:09,900
Chief Jian,

680
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:10,860
how about we meet directly

681
00:32:10,860 --> 00:32:12,210
at the police station?

682
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:15,070
I got an emergency call,

683
00:32:15,090 --> 00:32:16,490
so I'm outside right now.

684
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:17,660
Then how about

685
00:32:17,660 --> 00:32:19,660
we just wait for you at the station?

686
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,110
I'm sorry,

687
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:25,760
but my wife
hasn't been feeling well recently,

688
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,430
so I have to go home in a bit.

689
00:32:29,740 --> 00:32:30,380
How about this?

690
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,820
If you two don't mind,

691
00:32:32,170 --> 00:32:33,320
we can talk at my place.

692
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,320
What do you think?

693
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:36,440
That doesn't seem appropriate.

694
00:32:36,540 --> 00:32:37,780
It's fine.

695
00:32:37,950 --> 00:32:38,840
I'm the host,

696
00:32:38,970 --> 00:32:40,680
so it's only right to treat you to a meal.

697
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:41,720
Not to brag,

698
00:32:41,970 --> 00:32:43,880
but my wife is a really good cook.

699
00:32:43,910 --> 00:32:44,520
I mean it.

700
00:32:45,690 --> 00:32:46,750
Then it's settled.

701
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:47,500
I'll send the address

702
00:32:47,500 --> 00:32:48,960
to your phone number later.

703
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:49,640
Alright?

704
00:32:55,820 --> 00:32:57,020
Let's go to his house.

705
00:33:00,340 --> 00:33:01,060
602.

706
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:02,600
This should be the one.

707
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:05,430
Coming.

708
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,040
Hello.

709
00:33:12,260 --> 00:33:13,970
We are here for Chief Jian.

710
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:16,410
Officer Zhou.

711
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:18,930
Professor Jiang.

712
00:33:20,370 --> 00:33:21,210
Come on.

713
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,240
Please come on in.

714
00:33:23,730 --> 00:33:24,380
Come in.

715
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:26,670
I've got the slippers ready for you.

716
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,780
Something came up,
and Jian hasn't returned yet.

717
00:33:31,780 --> 00:33:32,490
Please, have a seat.

718
00:33:32,490 --> 00:33:34,050
I'll go make some tea for you.

719
00:33:34,050 --> 00:33:35,850
Please don't trouble yourself.

720
00:33:36,100 --> 00:33:37,290
I'm his wife.

721
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:38,430
You are so young.

722
00:33:38,540 --> 00:33:39,690
Just call me ma'am.

723
00:33:40,590 --> 00:33:41,310
Come on in.

724
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:42,740
Make yourselves at home.

725
00:33:44,070 --> 00:33:45,800
Please, come in and have a seat.

726
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,560
Funny, right?

727
00:34:19,030 --> 00:34:19,820
Who would hang their police uniform

728
00:34:19,820 --> 00:34:21,489
on the wall in their own home?

729
00:34:21,670 --> 00:34:23,330
Like some kind of narcissist.

730
00:34:23,610 --> 00:34:24,300
Not at all.

731
00:34:25,130 --> 00:34:27,090
Since his first day as a police officer,

732
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:28,420
Jian has had this habit.

733
00:34:28,690 --> 00:34:29,830
Every morning when he wakes up,

734
00:34:29,830 --> 00:34:30,900
he has to look at it

735
00:34:31,219 --> 00:34:32,219
to remind himself

736
00:34:32,370 --> 00:34:34,770
to be loyal to his duty
and work diligently.

737
00:34:35,610 --> 00:34:36,570
He also says

738
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:38,739
it's not safe for me to be
alone at home so often.

739
00:34:38,739 --> 00:34:40,500
By hanging a police uniform here,

740
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:41,830
even if a thief broke in,

741
00:34:41,909 --> 00:34:43,170
they wouldn't dare steal anything.

742
00:34:43,170 --> 00:34:44,780
He's just that kind of person.

743
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:46,900
Please excuse him.

744
00:34:48,130 --> 00:34:49,260
Here, have some tea.

745
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:51,960
By the way,

746
00:34:52,530 --> 00:34:54,219
what do you want to eat for lunch today?

747
00:34:54,219 --> 00:34:55,090
Tell me,

748
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,449
and I'll make it for you.

749
00:34:57,930 --> 00:34:58,970
We are not picky.

750
00:35:00,530 --> 00:35:01,590
Just not too spicy.

751
00:35:02,740 --> 00:35:04,170
I can help you.

752
00:35:04,820 --> 00:35:05,450
Sure.

753
00:35:05,690 --> 00:35:07,490
See if the dishes I prepared

754
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:08,740
suit your taste.

755
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,450
We don't often have young people over,

756
00:35:10,450 --> 00:35:12,050
so I don't know what you like.

757
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:15,050
Have some fruit first.

758
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:17,520
Let's go.

759
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,400
Make yourself comfortable.

760
00:35:32,780 --> 00:35:33,970
Jian told me

761
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:37,830
that you guys are from
the CIB of Haizhou City, right?

762
00:35:40,780 --> 00:35:42,510
Being a criminal investigator

763
00:35:42,980 --> 00:35:44,110
must be tiring, huh?

764
00:35:44,860 --> 00:35:45,570
It's alright.

765
00:35:45,570 --> 00:35:47,470
It's just there have been
quite a few cases lately.

766
00:35:47,470 --> 00:35:48,730
Jian is also like this,

767
00:35:49,260 --> 00:35:51,320
busy all day without a moment to rest.

768
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:53,830
That's what it's like

769
00:35:53,830 --> 00:35:55,090
to be a police officer—

770
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:57,890
working tirelessly around the clock.

771
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:03,690
By the way,

772
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:06,360
what case brought you guys

773
00:36:06,570 --> 00:36:07,820
all the way here?

774
00:36:12,150 --> 00:36:14,660
It can't be that
Jian got into some trouble, right?

775
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:15,610
No, it's not.

776
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:28,890
The perpetrator may not necessarily have
a deficiency in romantic relationships.

777
00:37:28,890 --> 00:37:30,820
Rather, the issue lies in the mother-child
relationship from his early years.

778
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:32,120
He grew up in a single-parent household,

779
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:33,720
raised solely by his mother,

780
00:37:34,430 --> 00:37:37,040
and he developed very serious
psychological problems.

781
00:37:37,040 --> 00:37:38,180
It's also highly likely that

782
00:37:38,180 --> 00:37:39,490
he experienced betrayal,

783
00:37:39,490 --> 00:37:41,550
abandonment, or abuse by his mother,

784
00:37:41,700 --> 00:37:43,190
which led to a distorted personality.

785
00:37:43,190 --> 00:37:44,660
While obsessed with women,

786
00:37:44,660 --> 00:37:47,060
he also harbors extreme hatred
toward them.

787
00:37:47,060 --> 00:37:47,940
When Zhen

788
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:49,420
was making clothes

789
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:50,970
and doing handicrafts,

790
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:53,910
that child would watch her.

791
00:37:54,650 --> 00:37:56,250
Zhen liked to play the piano,

792
00:37:56,470 --> 00:37:57,940
and the child liked to listen to it.

793
00:37:57,940 --> 00:37:59,830
The police officer
who saved Qi Zhen back then

794
00:37:59,830 --> 00:38:01,120
was called Jian Liang.

795
00:38:01,550 --> 00:38:03,350
When I went to the hospital again,

796
00:38:03,350 --> 00:38:04,380
Zhen was gone.

797
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:05,060
This person

798
00:38:05,610 --> 00:38:08,010
harbors extreme hatred toward the police.

799
00:38:09,570 --> 00:38:10,430
Professor Jiang.

800
00:38:10,430 --> 00:38:11,390
But I always feel

801
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:12,750
that she's not dead—

802
00:38:12,970 --> 00:38:14,300
that she's still alive.

803
00:38:19,980 --> 00:38:20,730
It's okay. It's okay.

804
00:38:20,730 --> 00:38:21,440
I'm sorry.

805
00:38:23,010 --> 00:38:23,610
It's okay.

806
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,840
It's okay. It doesn't hurt much.

807
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:28,260
I just wanted to bring the soup over here

808
00:38:28,700 --> 00:38:30,650
to free up the stove for cooking.

809
00:38:30,680 --> 00:38:31,540
I didn't expect

810
00:38:31,860 --> 00:38:32,740
it to slip.

811
00:38:33,150 --> 00:38:33,900
I'm sorry.

812
00:38:34,380 --> 00:38:35,300
Do you have ice cubes?

813
00:38:35,300 --> 00:38:35,940
I don't.

814
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,530
Maybe you should go to the hospital.

815
00:38:38,530 --> 00:38:40,930
Please go to the hospital right away,
okay?

816
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,610
I'm really okay, ma'am.

817
00:38:44,290 --> 00:38:45,380
I've been calling you ma'am.

818
00:38:45,380 --> 00:38:46,300
I forgot to ask—

819
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:48,160
what is your last name?

820
00:38:49,430 --> 00:38:50,710
M-My last name is Xie.

821
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,660
What about your full name?

822
00:38:57,670 --> 00:38:58,550
Get out.

823
00:38:58,940 --> 00:38:59,800
Get out of here.

824
00:38:59,950 --> 00:39:00,950
Calm down, ma'am.

825
00:39:00,980 --> 00:39:02,380
Put the knife down first.

826
00:39:03,620 --> 00:39:04,240
Put the knife down.

827
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:05,110
Get out of here!

828
00:39:05,130 --> 00:39:06,220
Get out!

829
00:39:06,380 --> 00:39:07,420
Leave my house!

830
00:39:08,670 --> 00:39:10,070
You're not welcome here!

831
00:39:10,990 --> 00:39:12,720
Jian knows nothing about this!

832
00:39:12,730 --> 00:39:13,520
She was

833
00:39:13,730 --> 00:39:14,830
sent to the hospital because

834
00:39:14,830 --> 00:39:16,280
she tried to commit suicide.

835
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:17,610
By slitting her wrists.

836
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,420
You don't have ice—

837
00:39:19,980 --> 00:39:21,820
do you have anything else frozen?

838
00:39:21,820 --> 00:39:22,680
Please get it for me.

839
00:39:22,680 --> 00:39:23,970
Get out of here, do you hear me?

840
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:24,740
Get out!

841
00:39:24,770 --> 00:39:25,480
Qi Zhen!

842
00:39:26,380 --> 00:39:28,640
If you want to continue your current life

843
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:30,980
and don't want to cause trouble
for Chief Jian,

844
00:39:30,980 --> 00:39:32,530
put down the knife in your hand.

845
00:39:32,530 --> 00:39:33,860
Do not try to provoke me.

846
00:39:35,300 --> 00:39:36,780
No. No.

847
00:39:37,150 --> 00:39:38,900
Don't tell him!

848
00:39:39,450 --> 00:39:40,530
No, no, I mean...

849
00:39:40,650 --> 00:39:41,940
I'm not Qi Zhen!

850
00:39:42,020 --> 00:39:43,270
I'm not Qi Zhen!

851
00:39:43,290 --> 00:39:44,350
My name is Xie Meng!

852
00:39:44,470 --> 00:39:45,810
You've got the wrong person!

853
00:39:45,810 --> 00:39:46,810
Please calm down.

854
00:39:47,220 --> 00:39:48,240
Put the knife down first.

855
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:49,110
Let's talk,

856
00:39:49,300 --> 00:39:49,900
okay?

857
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:52,990
Why...

858
00:39:53,700 --> 00:39:55,700
Why did you find this place?

859
00:39:56,350 --> 00:39:56,790
You...

860
00:39:57,230 --> 00:39:58,290
You are his people?

861
00:39:59,650 --> 00:40:00,450
Who are you?

862
00:40:01,010 --> 00:40:02,870
You are not police at all, are you?

863
00:40:04,420 --> 00:40:05,480
You are his people.

864
00:40:06,450 --> 00:40:07,900
He sent you to take me

865
00:40:08,050 --> 00:40:09,780
and my son back, didn't he?

866
00:40:10,890 --> 00:40:11,660
Who is he?

867
00:40:12,220 --> 00:40:13,360
Who wants to catch you?

868
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,550
Your son is Qi Yan,

869
00:40:14,740 --> 00:40:15,170
right?

870
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:15,950
Where is he?

871
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:19,420
You are too late.

872
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,630
Go back and tell him

873
00:40:22,430 --> 00:40:23,870
that I strangled his son.

874
00:40:25,030 --> 00:40:26,660
His son has long been dead.

875
00:40:27,450 --> 00:40:28,020
I should never have

876
00:40:28,020 --> 00:40:29,530
expected anything good from that child

877
00:40:29,530 --> 00:40:31,060
tainted with filthy blood.

878
00:40:31,650 --> 00:40:33,340
He's a vile creature,

879
00:40:33,340 --> 00:40:35,510
and his son is no better!

880
00:40:35,530 --> 00:40:36,930
They both deserve to die!

881
00:40:37,970 --> 00:40:39,900
You deserve to die too!

882
00:40:42,270 --> 00:40:44,020
Go back and tell him

883
00:40:44,750 --> 00:40:46,610
that I will never go back with you.

884
00:40:47,170 --> 00:40:49,050
And I'm not afraid of him anymore.

885
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:52,280
Jian Liang is a clean person.

886
00:40:52,510 --> 00:40:54,470
If you dare to lay a finger on him,

887
00:40:56,300 --> 00:40:57,900
I will fight you to the death.

888
00:40:58,350 --> 00:40:59,020
Tell me,

889
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:00,980
who is Qi Yan's father?

890
00:41:03,970 --> 00:41:05,180
Y-You...

891
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:06,360
You don't know?

892
00:41:08,610 --> 00:41:10,450
You weren't sent by him?

893
00:41:10,700 --> 00:41:11,380
Qi Zhen.

894
00:41:11,530 --> 00:41:12,820
I am Zhou Jin from
the Criminal Investigation Brigade

895
00:41:12,820 --> 00:41:14,750
of Nancheng Branch, Haizhou City.

896
00:41:15,570 --> 00:41:17,540
There's been a recent case in Haizhou,

897
00:41:17,540 --> 00:41:18,750
and your son, Qi Yan,

898
00:41:18,970 --> 00:41:20,340
is a key suspect.

899
00:41:20,380 --> 00:41:21,170
We actually came today

900
00:41:21,170 --> 00:41:22,490
to talk to Jian Liang

901
00:41:22,540 --> 00:41:23,530
and get your information.

902
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:24,610
Don't tell me...

903
00:41:24,610 --> 00:41:27,090
Don't tell me anything about him anymore!

904
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,880
Don't bring him up to me again!

905
00:41:29,170 --> 00:41:31,340
Don't bring him up to me again!

906
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:34,650
But he is your son.

907
00:41:34,650 --> 00:41:35,860
Just because I gave birth to him,

908
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:37,420
do I have to pay for his sins?

909
00:41:40,530 --> 00:41:41,170
Alright.

910
00:41:41,820 --> 00:41:42,450
Alright.

911
00:41:42,940 --> 00:41:43,940
If I die,

912
00:41:44,210 --> 00:41:46,040
you won't come back, will you?

913
00:41:46,770 --> 00:41:47,850
If I die,

914
00:41:48,650 --> 00:41:50,850
Jian Liang will be left in peace, right?

915
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:52,940
Alright...

916
00:41:55,190 --> 00:41:55,900
Alright...

917
00:41:57,420 --> 00:41:58,170
Alright...

918
00:42:03,530 --> 00:42:04,170
Hansheng.

919
00:42:04,380 --> 00:42:05,300
I'm sorry.

920
00:42:06,490 --> 00:42:08,140
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

921
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:23,170
This lock...

922
00:42:23,660 --> 00:42:25,190
This lock won't open again.

923
00:42:27,980 --> 00:42:28,830
Honey,

924
00:42:29,490 --> 00:42:31,020
this lock won't open again.

925
00:42:32,340 --> 00:42:33,870
Can you open the door for me?

926
00:42:34,450 --> 00:42:35,080
Oh, alright.

927
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:35,870
It's open.

928
00:42:37,580 --> 00:42:39,470
Honey, this door lock

929
00:42:39,490 --> 00:42:41,020
really needs to be changed.

930
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:48,560
You arrived even earlier...

931
00:42:49,510 --> 00:42:50,050
Than me.

932
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:52,720
W-What's wrong?

933
00:42:59,130 --> 00:42:59,860
Are you okay?

934
00:43:03,530 --> 00:43:03,990
This...

935
00:43:06,220 --> 00:43:07,220
What happened?
